{
  "doc_id": "812",
  "text": "There is consensus over CT use in the initial evaluation of the pediatric patients with moderate to severe head traumas, whereas the debate is still going for minor TBI category even though many studies have already been conducted [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . There is the scarce amount of studies to evaluate the necessity of repeat CT scan in TBI. There is a risk of exposure to high iodising radiation (median dose = 20 mGy, in some cases it may pass over 40 mGy) during brain CT scans [8-11, 20, 21] .",
